SIMPLE: languishing
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Languishing
<hw>Lan"guish*ing</hw>, <pos>a.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Becoming languid
and weak; pining; losing health and strength.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Amorously pensive; indicating melancholy; <as>as,
<ex>languishing</ex> eyes, or look</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>Suffering neglect; neglected.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><sn>4.</sn> <def>Continuing in a weak or deteriorating state;
lingering.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Languishingly</ent>⟦br⟧
